.TH DABTRFS 1 "2025-12-29" "dumbass-tree" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dabtrfs \- dumbass-friendly Btrfs helper (Linux)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dabtrfs
[\-\-dry-run] [\-\-verbose]
.I <command>
[\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
dabtrfs wraps common btrfs(8) workflows: subvolumes, snapshots, scrub, balance, and mounting with compression.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B dabtrfs subvol create \fIpath\fR
Create subvolume.
.TP
.B dabtrfs subvol list \fImountpoint\fR
List subvolumes.
.TP
.B dabtrfs snapshot \fIsrc\fR \fIdst\fR [\-\-readonly]
Create snapshot.
.TP
.B dabtrfs scrub start|status \fImountpoint\fR
Start scrub or show status.
.TP
.B dabtrfs balance start \fImountpoint\fR [\-\-dusage PCT] [\-\-musage PCT]
Start a filtered balance.
.TP
.B dabtrfs df \fImountpoint\fR
Show filesystem usage.
.TP
.B dabtrfs mount \fIdevice\fR \fImountpoint\fR [\-\-compress ALG] [\-\-noatime]
Mount with common options.
.SH SEE ALSO
btrfs(8), mkfs.btrfs(8)
